Relocate the nommu RISC-V kernel to chiron's RAM base (0x80000000).

CONFIG_PAGE_OFFSET is the nommu RAM/link base. bbl (--with-mem-start=0x80000000)
occupies the first 2 MB of DRAM for itself and places the payload (vmlinux) at
+0x200000; the kernel MUST be linked at 0x80200000 to match, or vmlinux's entry
point collides with bbl's own base (0x80000000) and every internal absolute
address in vmlinux is wrong relative to where bbl actually placed those bytes
-- the hart doesn't crash, it just executes whatever real function happens to
live at the (wrong) computed address forever, which looks like a silent hang
with zero console output (observed: all harts looping inside an unrelated
mm/rhashtable.c function).

This kernel version's own upstream default is 0x80000000 (not the 0x10200000
some older versions used) -- update the exact default value the patch targets
if it drifts again; the point is 0x80200000, always headroom-corrected for
bbl's 2 MB.

Apply from the linux/ source tree:  patch -p1 < this_file
Then: make olddefconfig  (confirm CONFIG_PAGE_OFFSET=0x80200000)

--- a/arch/riscv/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/riscv/Kconfig
@@ -178,7 +178,7 @@ config PAGE_OFFSET
 	hex
 	default 0xC0000000 if 32BIT
-	default 0x80000000 if 64BIT && !MMU
+	default 0x80200000 if 64BIT && !MMU
 	default 0xff60000000000000 if 64BIT
